expression: "snapshot_help(&[\"edit\"])"
---
Structural editing of code symbols

Usage: normalize edit [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  delete   Delete a symbol.
           
           With `--each`, deletes the symbol from every file matching `--only` that contains it —
           useful for removing a trait method from all implementations at once.
  replace  Replace a symbol with new content.
           
           With `--each`, replaces the symbol in every file matching `--only` that contains it —
           useful for updating a trait method body across all implementations at once.
  swap     Swap two symbols
  insert   Insert content relative to a symbol.
           
           With `--each`, applies the insert to every file matching `--only` that contains
           the symbol — useful for adding a method to all implementations of a trait.
  undo     Undo the last N edits
  redo     Redo the last undone edit
  goto     Jump to a specific shadow commit
  batch    Apply batch edits from JSON file
  history  View shadow git edit history
  help     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --jsonl                      Output one JSON object per line (for arrays)
      --pretty                     Human-friendly output with colors and formatting
      --compact                    Compact output without colors (overrides TTY detection)
      --json                       Output machine-readable JSON
      --jq <jq>                    Filter output through jq expression
      --input-schema               Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's input parameters and exit
      --output-schema              Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's return type and exit
      --params-json <params-json>  Provide all parameters as a JSON object instead of individual flags
  -h, --help                       Print help
  -V, --version                    Print version
